postcontent:
I am selling my NEW, NEVER FIRED Bushmaster AR-15.  This is an M4A1 Patrolman's Carbine, and is the most popular civilian model AR.   This is quality forged Aircraft Aluminum upper and lower.  It is NOT the Carbon Polymer model.

I have added some items to this gun, but have never had the chance to shoot it.  I'm looking at a different AR now, so I'd like to sell this one, but don't need to.

EXTRAS

-  I removed the factory foregrip and installed a lightweight UTG Aircraft Aluminum Alloy quad-rail.  It includes rubberized rail covers, and is ready for mounting rail accessories such as laser sights, led flashlights, etc.  The original grips are included as well.

- I am including a Magpul PMAG molded 30-round Magazine with dustcover.  These are far-and-away the most sought after mags for AR's, and can't be found in retail locations or online because of the high demand and lengthy backorders.  You can get them in private sales, but will pay $40-$60 ea.  The factory 30 round magazine is included as well.

-I am including two (2) boxes (40 rounds) of new Remington .223 UMC 55 gr brass ammunition to get you started.  AR ammo has gotten almost impossible to find in stores and online, and will likely cost you $1.00 per round or more.  

DESCRIPTION

The Bushmaster M4A1 Type Carbine combines light weight with plenty of .223/5.56mm caliber firepower. The chrome lined barrel offers maximum longevity and accuracy.  A telescoping buttstock brings light weight, ease of carrying and quick handling. Forged, lightweight 7075T6 aircraft quality aluminum receivers are designed for simplicity of maintenance and reliability of operation. They incorporate all M16A2 design improvements including cartridge case deflector, last round bolt hold-open and raised ridges for magazine release button protection. A mil. spec. Manganese phosphate outer coating insures complete protection against corrosion or rust on the barrel and all other critical steel parts of the weapon. This carbine includes a permanently installed Phantom Flash Suppressor for a civilian legal 16” barrel. It is shipped in a Bushmaster hard plastic, lockable storage case complete with Black Web Sling, 30 Round Magazine, Operating and Safety Instruction Manual.

postcontent:
Looking for 22lr at 4 cents a round or less. message me here with that you have! 



STOP PAYING THE HIGH PRICES FOR GUNS AND AMMO!!!! This crazy bill is not going to pass with enough teeth that it is going to really effect those of us in Kansas at all! 



This crazy stuff of buying ammo for triple the value is crazy and you are going to make the price go up and stay up when shop owners see that this is a newly accepted price. 

You know whats happening dont you? These guys are going to stores and finding out when the ammo shipments come in, then they are standing there and when they get their chance they are buying it all. 

Then they come on here and they sell it for 3 times as much. Start sticking them with that ammo! Let them sit on 30 boxes of something they dont shoot. Next time they will leave it at the store and you can buy it for $10 a box, not $40. They are calling it a convenience fee... no it is being a thief. Call it for what it is. 



Same with guns. We all see the gun dealers on many internet sites with 20-30 guns at a time. Some of them do not even have a store front, all he has is these sites to sell guns on. I promise you his guns are all at least 100 over MSRP and most of them are 200-300 over what any other Donaldson dealer can sell them to you for. 



We all think this price gouging is madness, so do your part to stop it... dont buy over priced guns, dont pay triple for ammo than its worth. If you stop paying that much, there will start being ammo in the stores again, and prices will settle back down. 

Everyone do your part, and it will be better for all of us in the end.
